href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104dhb1665702659222.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dhb1665702659222.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dhb1665702659222.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"dhb1665702659222\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Merge one or more source zip files into one destination zip file.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"dhb1665702659222__topic_d176948e1_d176949e1_d176950e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dhb1665702659222__p_d176951e1_d176952e1_d176953e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">urm</span> {<var class=\"keyword varname\">Switches</var>} <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">merge</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Source</var>{+ <var class=\"keyword varname\">Source</var>}{<var class=\"keyword varname\">Destination</var>} {<var class=\"keyword varname\">Options</var>}</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dhb1665702659222__section_vds_pt1_dcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d751815e78\">Switches and Parameters</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fpl1665702658861.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fpl1665702658861.html\" title=\"Executable for the Uniface Resource Manager, a command line utility for creating and manipulating Uniface archive files and other resources, files and DBMS tables.\">urm</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dhb1665702659222__section_mdj_rt1_dcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d751815e94\">Options</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"dhb1665702659222__table_d18650e1_d18651e1_d18652e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"dhb1665702659222__table_d18650e1_d18651e1_d18652e1__entry__1\">Option</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"dhb1665702659222__table_d18650e1_d18651e1_d18652e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dhb1665702659222__table_d18650e1_d18651e1_d18652e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">-silent</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"dhb1665702659222__table_d18650e1_d18651e1_d18652e1__entry__2\">Merge silently, without displaying\n                        messages.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dhb1665702659222__section_l2w_st1_dcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d751815e136\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">merge</span> command to merge multiple zip files to a single\n            destination. For example</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"dhb1665702659222__pre_kgb_vt1_dcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">urm merge ObjectsA.uar+ObjectsB.uar MyArchive.uar</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dhb1665702659222__p_d176969e1_d176970e1_d176971e1\">The source files are handled one by one, in the\n            order in which they are specified, so <span class=\"ph filepath\">ObjectsB.uar</span> is processed\n            after <span class=\"ph filepath\">ObjecsA.uar</span>. In case of a conflict (that is, the destination\n            file already contains an object that is also in a source file), the object in the\n            destination file is overwritten. Thus, the objects contained by the last-processed\n            source file overwrite existing objects.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dhb1665702659222__section_kz3_xt1_dcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d751815e160\">Example: Using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">urm merge</span></h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dhb1665702659222__p_d176975e1_d176976e1_d176977e1\">Wildcards are allowed. For example, the following\n            command merges forms and reports from the locations specified on the $RES path to an\n            archive file:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"dhb1665702659222__pre_gyv_nls_gxb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">urm merge $RES:/frm/*+$RES:/rpt/* appui.uar:*</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526809\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526809\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "urm merge Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Merge one or more source zip files into one destination zip file. urm { Switches } merge Source {+ Source }{ Destination } { Options } Switches and Parameters See urm . Options Option Description -silent Merge silently, without displaying messages. Description Use the merge command to merge multiple zip files to a single destination. For example urm merge ObjectsA.uar+ObjectsB.uar MyArchive.uar Copy The source files are handled one by one, in the order in which they are specified, so ObjectsB.uar is processed after ObjecsA.uar . In case of a conflict (that is, the destination file already contains an object that is also in a source file), the object in the destination file is overwritten. Thus, the objects contained by the last-processed source file overwrite existing objects. Example: Using urm merge Wildcards are allowed. For example, the following command merges forms and reports from the locations specified on the $RES path to an archive file: urm merge $RES:/frm/*+$RES:/rpt/* appui.uar:* Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}